FOODBORNE ILLNESS - MALAYSIA: MUSSELS, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 20 Nov 2017 , 5:06 PM
Source: The Sun Daily [edited]
http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2017/11/20/128-come-down-food-poisoning-after-end-school-party


Three students from the Muar Vocational College here were admitted to hospital for severe food poisoning after consuming seafood at their end of school party last [Sat 18 Nov 2017].

Johor Health and Environment, Education and Information committee chairman Datuk Ayub Rahmat said the 3 were among 128 who came down with foodborne illness after consuming seafood at the party. "The 3 have been hospitalized but the others were given outpatient treatment and sent back. The initial investigation showed that mussels could have been the cause of the poisoning, " he said. "Samples from the food and water served, as well as swabs from the food handlers and the kitchen equipment, were sent to the Johor Baru Public Health Laboratory for analysis on [Mon 20 Nov 2017]" he said.

Ayub said the hostel's kitchen has been ordered closed for 3 days until [Tue 21 Nov 2017] under the Prevention and Control of Infectious Diseases Act 1988.

